subsection_content:
Subjects with TOS syndrome include:
Swimmers are considered a group of people susceptible to TOS syndrome
Athletes who play sports such as swimming, cricket, rugby...; Musicians such as violinists, flute players...; People whose jobs typically only involve certain manual activities such as mechanics, hairdressers, teachers, assembly line workers; People who lift weights incorrectly cause muscle imbalance; People who carry heavy loads cause muscle swelling, causing blood vessels and nerves to become entangled and compressed.
